sql:
SELECT AVG(temperature) AS average_temperature
FROM usage_data
WHERE weather_situation = 1;

SELECT date, total_count
FROM usage_data
ORDER BY date;

SELECT casual_users
FROM usage_data
WHERE date = '2023-10-01';

SELECT date, SUM(total_count) AS total_rentals
FROM usage_data
GROUP BY date;

SELECT date, total_count, average_rental_duration
FROM usage_data
ORDER BY date DESC;

external_knowledge:
- A substantial amount of data is defined as more than 10 recorded usage instances; 
- A holiday can be national, local, or a special event; 
- Weather situation refers to the condition of the weather at a given time, such as sunny, rainy, etc.

